{"workflow_number":127,"workflow_id":"gastro-liver-enzyme-review","title":"Liver enzyme review","specialty":"Gastroenterology","diagnosis":"Liver enzyme review documentation","research_status":"partial_source_support","research_status_label":"Partial source support","uae_applicability":"No exact UAE abnormal-liver-test guideline was identified. UK guidance requires UAE clinician review and local laboratory, imaging, and referral pathways.","uae_findings":[{"finding_type":"partial_applicability","evidence_basis":"Structured source status remains partial_exact_source_verified."}],"source_references":[{"source_resolves":true,"source_id":"bsg-abnormal-liver-blood-tests-2018","title":"Guidelines on the management of abnormal liver blood tests","issuing_organisation":"British Society of Gastroenterology","official_url":"https://www.bsg.org.uk/getmedia/b51bdc64-7145-43ad-828b-21f473b0a918/Guidelines-on-the-management-of-abnormal-liver-blood-tests.pdf","jurisdiction":"United Kingdom","sections":[{"section_id":"bsg-liver-tests-2018-standard-panel","heading":"Recommendation 1 — standard initial liver blood-test panel","locator":"PDF page 1; recommendations list","evidence_summary":"Supports clinician review of bilirubin and standard liver blood-test components; it does not provide patient-specific interpretation or diagnosis."},{"section_id":"bsg-liver-tests-2018-context-interpretation","heading":"Recommendations 2–3 — prior results and clinical context","locator":"PDF pages 8–9; lines 717–764","evidence_summary":"Requires review of previous results, past medical history, current condition, the specific abnormal analyte, and clinical context rather than inferring significance from magnitude alone."},{"section_id":"bsg-liver-tests-2018-clinical-history","heading":"Response to abnormal liver blood tests — clinical history","locator":"PDF page 10; lines 849–855","evidence_summary":"Supports age, hepatitis-risk context, jaundice, abdominal pain, weight loss, pruritus, comorbidity